@startuml nextflow_sequence

title Nextflow Metagenomics Pipeline v2.0 - Data Flow\nWith Contig Filtering and Dereplication

participant "FASTQ\nInput" as Input
participant "NANOPLOT" as QC
participant "FILTLONG" as Filter
participant "FLYE" as Assembly
participant "FILTER_CONTIGS\n⭐NEW" as FContig
participant "BWA" as Mapping
participant "METABAT2" as Bin1
participant "CONCOCT" as Bin2
participant "CHECKM" as QC2
participant "BIN_FILTER" as BFilter
participant "DREP\n⭐NEW" as Drep
participant "PROKKA" as Prokka
participant "ABRICATE" as Abr
participant "DEEPARG" as Deep
participant "Results" as Results

Input -> QC: Raw FASTQ reads
QC -> Filter: Quality report
Filter -> Assembly: Filtered reads\n(>1000bp, Q>10)

Assembly -> FContig: Raw assembly\n(all contigs)

note right of FContig
  **NEW STEP**
  seqkit filters contigs:
  - Remove < 1000bp
  - Generate stats report
  
  Reduces noise for binning
end note

FContig -> Mapping: Filtered assembly\n(contigs ≥1000bp)
FContig -> Bin1: Filtered contigs
FContig -> Bin2: Filtered contigs

Mapping -> Bin1: BAM + coverage
Mapping -> Bin2: BAM + coverage

note right of Bin1
  METABAT2 on filtered contigs:
  Additional filter: ≥2500bp
  
  Creates bins based on:
  - Coverage patterns
  - Tetranucleotide frequency
end note

Bin1 -> QC2: MetaBAT2 bins\n(multiple bins)

note right of Bin2
  CONCOCT on filtered contigs:
  Chunks contigs (10kb)
  Additional filter: ≥1000bp
  
  May create 0-N bins
end note

Bin2 -> QC2: CONCOCT bins\n(0 or more bins)

QC2 -> BFilter: All bins +\nquality metrics

note right of BFilter
  **Optional filtering**
  (--skip_bin_quality_filter)
  
  Default thresholds:
  - Completeness >50%
  - Contamination <10%
  
  Removes:
  - lowDepth, tooShort
  - unbinned sequences
  - empty bins
end note

BFilter -> Drep: Quality bins from\nMetaBAT2 + CONCOCT

note right of Drep
  **NEW STEP**
  Genome dereplication:
  - Cluster by ANI (0.95)
  - Select best representative
  - Remove near-duplicates
  
  Input: All quality bins
  Output: Dereplicated set
end note

Drep -> Prokka: Dereplicated bins\n(unique genomes)
Drep -> Abr: Dereplicated bins
Drep -> Deep: Dereplicated bins

note over Prokka, Deep
  **Per-Bin Annotation**
  Each dereplicated bin
  processed in parallel
end note

Prokka -> Results: Per-bin annotation\n(GFF, FAA, GBK)
Abr -> Results: Per-bin AMR genes\n(CARD database)
Deep -> Results: Per-bin ARG predictions\n(ML-based)

note over Results
  **Organized Results**
  /prokka/bin_name/
  /abricate/bin_name/
  /deeparg/bin_name/
  
  Each genome tracked separately
  No gene mixing between organisms
end note

@enduml
